The paper discusses techniques for implementing protocols among threads, which is a topic related to programming languages (cs.PL), distributed computing (cs.DC), software engineering (cs.SE), data structures (cs.DS), and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of domain-specific languages (DSL) is also a common theme in programming languages and software engineering research. Therefore, cs.PL and cs.SE are the most likely categories, followed by cs.DC, cs.DS, and cs.LO.
